\newtheorem{lemma}{Lemma}
\begin{lemma}\label{usolution}$u_{ASE}^*$ is the solution of the equation $\int_0^\infty  {\frac{{1}}{z}} \frac{{1 - e^{ - z\frac{1}{u} + z}  - z\frac{1}{u}e^{ - z\frac{1}{u} + z} }}{{e^{ - z}  + z^{\frac{2}{\alpha }} \gamma \left( {1 - \frac{2}{\alpha },z} \right)}}dz=0$. There is a unique solution for this equation, which satisfies $u\in[0,1]$ and can be derived through the bisection method.
